The perjury trial of former News of the World editor Andy Coulson in Scotland is due to start later this week.The 47-year-old is accused of committing perjury in the 2010 trial of former MSP Tommy Sheridan.Coulson, who denies the allegation, appeared at the High Court in Edinburgh today.Judge Lord Burns set a date for the trial to begin on Friday May 15 following today's hearing.